This guide will show you how to configure BTT Eddy Tap with Klipper without needing Eddy_NG. Unfortunately, Eddy_NG has many issues when homeing (at least in my experience). The printer used in this guide is a Sovol SV08 with a mainline, as per Rappetor's guide. It's recommended to review how to upload the Katapult to the BTT Eddy to facilitate updating its Klipper firmware:
https://github.com/Rappetor/katapult-on-btt-eddy

It is suggested to periodically review the changes in the Klipper 3D Eddy documentation on which I base the calibration and configuration of this guide:
https://www.klipper3d.org/Eddy_Probe.html

I must clarify that any failure caused by following this guide is not my responsibility or that of the GitHub sites Rappetor, Klipper3D, or ThePrintasaurus.

Sources used:

https://github.com/ThePrintasaurus/SV08-Eddy-NG
https://github.com/Rappetor/Sovol-SV08-Mainline
https://github.com/klipper3d/klipper
